Oftentimes we think that if we do the right things, people will like us. The funny thing is when you do the right things, there will be people who'll dislike you. But know that there are people who'll like working with you. There will be people who'll rally behind you. Some people see and understand what you are bringing to the table. When working, ask yourself "What value am I adding here? How can I help fast-track the process? How can I help manage the timelines? How can I contribute to managing the company's resources better?". You're not here to please everyone. You're here to do what must be done.
